  '77777777-7777-7777-7777-700000000006',
  'Building ToquePlay: Lessons from Developing a Music Streaming Platform in Angola',
  'building-toqueplay-music-streaming-angola-lessons',
  '66666666-6666-6666-6666-600000000004',
  'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1511671782779-c97d3d27a1d4?w=1200&h=600&fit=crop',
  'Rafael Pilartes',
  '/t-avt-1.png',
  'ToquePlay was my first large-scale product — a music streaming and digital sales platform for Angolan artists. Here are the real technical decisions, mistakes, and lessons from building it with React.js, React Native, Node.js, and Firebase.',
  $$ {"raw": "", "text": "## Building for a Market That Is Often Ignored\n\nAngola has a vibrant music scene — Kuduro, Semba, Afrohouse — but Angolan artists had no dedicated platform to sell and stream their music. ToquePlay was built to fill that gap.\n\nAs the lead technical contributor at Toque Mediar, I was responsible for the full stack: web app, mobile app, and backend.\n\n### The Stack\n\n- **Frontend Web:** React.js with a custom component library\n- **Mobile:** React Native (iOS + Android)\n- **Backend:** Node.js with Firebase Cloud Functions\n- **Database & Auth:** Firebase Firestore + Firebase Authentication\n- **Storage:** Firebase Storage for audio files and artwork\n\n### The Biggest Technical Challenge: Audio Streaming\n\nStreaming audio is fundamentally different from loading images or text. You need:\n1. **Progressive loading** — start playing before the full file downloads\n2. **Background playback** — music should continue when the app is backgrounded\n3. **Offline caching** — users on slow networks need to pre-download tracks\n\nFor React Native, I used `react-native-track-player` — the only library that handles all three reliably.\n\n```typescript\n// Setting up the audio player\nimport TrackPlayer, { Capability } from 'react-native-track-player';\n\nexport async function setupPlayer() {\n  await TrackPlayer.setupPlayer();\n  await TrackPlayer.updateOptions({\n    capabilities: [\n      Capability.Play,\n      Capability.Pause,\n      Capability.SkipToNext,\n      Capability.SkipToPrevious,\n      Capability.SeekTo,\n    ],\n    compactCapabilities: [Capability.Play, Capability.Pause],\n  });\n}\n```\n\n### Firebase Storage Costs: The Lesson I Learned the Hard Way\n\nAudio files are large. A 5-minute track at 320kbps is ~12MB. With 500 tracks and 1,000 daily active users each streaming 10 songs, you are looking at **60GB of egress per day**.\n\nFirebase Storage charges for egress. We hit an unexpected bill in month 2.\n\n**The fix:** Implement a CDN layer (Cloudflare) in front of Firebase Storage. Cached audio files serve from the edge at near-zero cost. Egress costs dropped by 85%.\n\n### The Artist Dashboard\n\nBeyond the streaming experience, artists needed analytics: plays, downloads, revenue. I built a real-time dashboard using Firestore aggregation queries and React recharts.\n\n### What I Would Do Differently\n\n1. **Start with a CDN from day one** — do not wait for the bill\n2. **Separate the artist portal from the listener app** — they have completely different UX needs\n3. **Use Firestore rules aggressively** — security should be enforced at the database level, not just the API\n\nToquePlay taught me that building for an underserved market is both a technical and a cultural challenge. Understanding your users is as important as understanding your stack."} $$::jsonb,
  '2024-08-20'
)
ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING;

